ENTRY       EC 3.6.4.5                  Enzyme
NAME        minus-end-directed kinesin ATPase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on acid anhydrides;
            Acting on acid anhydrides to facilitate cellular and subcellular movement
SYSNAME     kinesin ATP phosphohydrolase (minus-end-directed)
REACTION    ATP + H2O = ADP + phosphate [RN:R00086]
ALL_REAC    R00086
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009]
COMMENT     Structurally almost identical to EC 3.6.4.3 (microtubule-severing ATPase) but the movement it catalyses is towards the minus end of microtubules.
